INSERT INTO `qna` VALUES (1,'What is the main problem that YogyaBano\'s platform aims to address?','YogyaBano\'s platform aims to address issues such as lack of personalization in training programs, the need for continuous and spaced learning, making learning a habit, and reducing friction in accessing e-learning content.','sivasir','None'),(2,'How does YogyaBano enhance the learning experience for blue-collar and grey-collar workers?','YogyaBano enhances the learning experience by offering AI-assisted training platforms that launch training programs quickly, provide content in 11 different Indian languages, and use WhatsApp and voicebot for engagement and analytics.','sivasir','None'),(3,'What are some of the upcoming features planned for the YogyaBano platform?','Upcoming features for the YogyaBano platform include a scheduler for alerts and tips, a virtual AI coach, gamification elements like challenges and rewards, and hyper-personalization of content using AI/ML.','sivasir','None'),(4,'What is an example of a one-month training schedule using YogyaBano?','An example of a one-month training schedule includes an introduction to the module with a welcome video on Day 0, learning various concepts and engaging in quizzes throughout the month, and ending with feedback collection and final evaluation on Day 30.','sivasir','None'),(5,'Who is the founder of YogyaBano and what is his background?','The founder of YogyaBano is Siva Cotipalli, who has close to 15 years of experience as an entrepreneur in digital and fintech sectors. He is an alumnus of BITS Pilani, IIM-Kozhikode, and the London School of Economics, and has worked with Infosys, Oracle, and Gates Foundation.','sivasir','None'),(6,'What are the key differences between a \'store\' and a \'brand\' as outlined in the text?','A \'store\' is a general entity without unique identifiable qualities, while a \'brand\' has definable qualities that create a perception in the customer\'s mind, known as brand equity. A brand projects specific aspects of merchandise or customer service as brand quality.','test','None'),(7,'What are the new 4 C\'s of jewellery retailing introduced in the text?','The new 4 C\'s of jewellery retailing are Cost, Confidence, Convenience, and Customer Service. These factors play a crucial role in influencing a customer\'s purchase decision in the jewellery market.','test','None'),(8,'How can jewellery retailers improve parking facilities for their showrooms, according to the text?','Jewellery retailers can improve parking facilities by providing their own parking lot, leasing nearby parking spaces, coordinating with neighboring shops for shared parking, guiding customers to nearby paid parking, creating a parking pool with other retailers, utilizing mall parking, or offering valet parking services.','test','None'),(9,'Explain the significance of window displays in jewellery showrooms as described in the text.','Window displays are crucial because they help jewellery gain attention and value. They curate the best collections, increase sales by showcasing designs under spotlights, and attract passers-by with visually appealing arrangements that highlight select pieces.','test','None'),(10,'What are some strategies mentioned in the text to retain customers at a jewellery showroom?','Strategies for customer retention include providing excellent customer service, offering a superior shopping experience, eliminating pain points for customers, giving personal care and attention, implementing loyalty and referral programs, and engaging customers regularly with personalized communication and exclusive offers.','test','None'),(11,'What are the key components of the V-Mart Ethics Framework?','The V-Mart Ethics Framework consists of Company Values, Code of Conduct, Loss Prevention, Prevention of Sexual Harassment, and Whistleblower Evaluation.','vmartethics','https://salescoach-yb.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/audio/output_20250130054647.mp3'),(12,'Who are the key members of the Central Ethics Committee at V-Mart?','The key members of the Central Ethics Committee at V-Mart include Mrs. Anjali Goel and Mr. Anand Agarwal as Presiding Officers, Mrs. Sonal Singh as the Ethics Counselor, and Mr. Karun Kumar as the Governing Officer.','vmartethics','https://salescoach-yb.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/audio/output_20250130054651.mp3'),(13,'What actions are considered misconduct under V-Mart\'s Code of Conduct for Workplace Discipline?','Misconduct under V-Mart\'s Code of Conduct includes not following shift timings, taking unapproved leaves, being dishonest, theft, negligence, possession of drugs or alcohol at the workplace, insubordination, and violating safety rules.','vmartethics','https://salescoach-yb.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/audio/output_20250130054653.mp3'),(14,'How does V-Mart address incidents related to sexual harassment?','V-Mart addresses sexual harassment incidents through an Internal Committee, which investigates complaints received via ic@vmart.co.in. Investigators are nominated by the HO-ICC, conduct investigations, and report findings to take appropriate action.','vmartethics','https://salescoach-yb.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/audio/output_20250130054656.mp3'),(15,'What is the role of the whistleblower policy at V-Mart, and how should employees report misconduct?','The whistleblower policy at V-Mart encourages employees to report any fraud, unethical activities, or misconduct. Reports can be made anonymously to the Vigilance Officer via vigilance.officer@vmartretail.com or speakup@vmart.co.in. If issues involve senior management, reports can be sent to the Chairman of the Audit Committee.','vmartethics','https://salescoach-yb.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/audio/output_20250130054658.mp3'),(16,'What are the key components of the V-Mart Ethics Framework?','The key components of the V-Mart Ethics Framework include Company Values, Code of Conduct, Loss Prevention, Prevention of Sexual Harassment, and Whistleblower Policy.','vmartethics','https://salescoach-yb.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/audio/output_20250130054702.mp3'),(17,'Who are the primary contacts for ethics-related grievances at V-Mart?','Ethics-related grievances can be addressed to Mrs. Anjali Goel (anjali@vmart.co.in), Mr. Anand Agarwal (anand.agarwal@vmart.co.in), Mrs. Sonal Singh (Sonal.singh@vmartretail.com), or Mr. Karun Kumar (karun.kumar@vmartretail.com). Grievances can also be sent to speakup@vmart.co.in.','vmartethics','https://salescoach-yb.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/audio/output_20250130054704.mp3'),(18,'What steps are involved in the investigation process according to the V-Mart Ethics Framework?','The investigation process involves reporting the incident, initial meeting and assessment, assigning investigators, gathering evidence, conducting interviews, preparing a report of investigation, holding a conduct hearing, and taking appropriate action based on the findings.','vmartethics','https://salescoach-yb.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/audio/output_20250130054706.mp3'),(19,'Describe the role of the Ethics Committee in V-Mart\'s organizational structure.','The Ethics Committee is responsible for aligning workplace practices with the code of conduct and statutory compliance. Its scope includes training, investigating grievances, conducting confidential hearings, closing investigations within TAT, taking disciplinary actions, and conducting quarterly audits.','vmartethics','https://salescoach-yb.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/audio/output_20250130054709.mp3'),(20,'What measures does V-Mart employ to prevent and address sexual harassment in the workplace?','V-Mart employs measures such as a clear definition of sexual harassment, a policy covering various forms of employment, a structured complaint process, confidentiality in handling complaints, and a designated internal committee to investigate and address incidents.','vmartethics','https://salescoach-yb.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/audio/output_20250130054712.mp3'),(21,'What are the main components of the V-Mart Ethics framework?','The main components of the V-Mart Ethics framework are Company Values, Code of Conduct, Loss Prevention, Feedback, Prevention of Sexual Harassment, and Whistleblower Evaluation.','vme','None'),(22,'What are the responsibilities of the Ethics Committee according to the V-Mart Ethics framework?','The Ethics Committee is responsible for aligning workplace practices with the code of conduct and statutory compliance, investigating grievances, conducting confidential hearings, closing investigations within TAT, taking disciplinarian action, conducting quarterly audits, and maintaining necessary documents.','vme','None'),(23,'What actions are considered misconduct under V-Mart\'s Code of Conduct?','Misconduct includes not following shift timings, taking unapproved leaves, being dishonest, theft or fraud, negligence, leaving the workplace without permission, obstructing others, not observing safety precautions, and bringing weapons to the workplace.','vme','None'),(24,'What measures does the Loss Prevention Policy include to minimize shrinkage at V-Mart?','The Loss Prevention Policy includes preventive measures such as understanding KRA/KPI, implementing SOPs, improving audit scores, and ensuring CCTV and sensormatic machines work smoothly. Detective measures include conducting stock and SOP audits regularly.','vme','None'),(25,'How does the Whistleblower Policy ensure the protection of individuals reporting unethical activities at V-Mart?','The Whistleblower Policy allows individuals to report incidents anonymously, ensuring their identity is kept confidential. It is the responsibility of management to protect whistleblowers from targeting and harassment, and the policy outlines specific disciplinary actions for individuals found guilty of misconduct.','vme','None'),(26,'What is the central thesis of \'The Psychology of Selling\' by Brian Tracy?','The central thesis of \'The Psychology of Selling\' is that effective selling involves understanding and leveraging the psychological motivations of buyers. The book provides strategies, techniques, and insights to help salespeople increase their sales by understanding customer needs, building trust, and using persuasive techniques to close deals.','swiss-beauty','None'),(27,'According to Brian Tracy, what is the \'Law of Cause and Effect\' and how does it relate to sales success?','The \'Law of Cause and Effect\' states that for every effect, there is a specific cause or causes. In the context of sales, it means that success is not accidental but results from specific actions and behaviors. By emulating the habits and strategies of successful salespeople, anyone can achieve similar results.','swiss-beauty','None'),(28,'How does Brian Tracy suggest salespeople should approach goal setting to achieve success?','Brian Tracy suggests that salespeople should set clear, written goals with specific deadlines and create detailed action plans to achieve them. This involves breaking down goals into smaller, manageable steps, prioritizing tasks, and taking consistent daily action towards these goals.','swiss-beauty','None'),(29,'What role does \'self-concept\' play in a salesperson\'s success, according to the book?','According to the book, \'self-concept\' is crucial in determining a salesperson\'s success. It is the bundle of beliefs that a person holds about themselves that affects their performance and behavior. A positive self-concept leads to higher self-esteem, which in turn boosts confidence and effectiveness in selling.','swiss-beauty','None'),(30,'What are some of the key buyer personality types identified by Brian Tracy, and how should salespeople adapt their approaches for each?','Brian Tracy identifies several buyer personality types, including the apathetic buyer, the self-actualizing buyer, the analytical buyer, the relater buyer, the driver buyer, and the socializer buyer. Salespeople should adapt their approaches by recognizing these types and tailoring their communication style, presentation, and closing techniques to match the buyer\'s preferences and motivations.','swiss-beauty','None'),(1742505128,'What role is Shariq Aftab applying for at Microsoft?','Shariq Aftab is applying for the Software Engineer role at Microsoft.','upsii',NULL),(1742505129,'What specific roles and technologies has Shariq Aftab worked with in his professional journey?','Shariq Aftab has worked in software development, focusing on backend engineering and machine learning. He has experience with Java and Python for developing scalable backend systems and has integrated advanced ML models into applications.','upsii',NULL),(1742505130,'What is Shariq Aftab\'s motivation for applying to the Software Engineer role at Microsoft?','Shariq Aftab is motivated by the opportunity to work on projects with a global impact and contribute to products and services that millions of people rely on daily. He is excited about the innovative and dynamic environment at Microsoft.','upsii',NULL),(1742505131,'How has Shariq Aftab demonstrated his ability to blend traditional software engineering with AI technologies?','Shariq Aftab has demonstrated this ability by developing a lip-syncing model using GANs and CNNs, which improved the accuracy and realism of video applications.','upsii',NULL),(1742505132,'What previous experience does Shariq Aftab have in building scalable backend systems?','Shariq Aftab has experience in building scalable backend systems at OpenInApp, where he was instrumental in optimizing performance and ensuring scalability while primarily using Java and Python.','upsii',NULL),(1742505133,'What academic background supports Shariq Aftab\'s professional journey in software development?','Shariq Aftab has a strong academic foundation in computer science, which he further developed through hands-on industry experience.','upsii',NULL),(1742505134,'What role is Shariq Aftab applying for at Microsoft?','Shariq Aftab is applying for the Software Engineer role at Microsoft.','upsii',NULL),(1742505135,'What are Shariq Aftab\'s main areas of expertise in software development?','Shariq Aftab\'s main areas of expertise in software development are backend engineering and machine learning.','upsii',NULL),(1742505136,'Which programming languages does Shariq Aftab primarily use for developing scalable backend systems?','Shariq Aftab primarily uses Java and Python for developing scalable backend systems.','upsii',NULL),(1742505137,'What specific project did Shariq Aftab work on that involved machine learning models?','Shariq Aftab worked on developing a lip-syncing model using GANs and CNNs to improve the accuracy and realism of video applications.','upsii',NULL),(1742505138,'What motivates Shariq Aftab about the prospect of working at Microsoft?','Shariq Aftab is motivated by the prospect of working on projects at Microsoft that have a global impact and contribute to products and services that millions of people rely on daily.','upsii',NULL),(1742505139,'What is the main challenge in blind face restoration as described in the article?','The main challenge in blind face restoration is the highly ill-posed nature of the problem, which arises from the loss of information due to degradation and the unknown specifics of the degradation. This leads to infinite plausible high-quality outputs from a low-quality input, making it difficult to achieve optimal restoration quality without additional guidance.','hi',NULL),(1742505140,'How does the CodeFormer approach aim to improve the robustness of blind face restoration?','CodeFormer improves the robustness of blind face restoration by casting the restoration as a code prediction task using a Transformer-based prediction network. This approach utilizes a learned discrete codebook prior in a small proxy space to reduce uncertainty and ambiguity in the restoration mapping, while also providing rich visual atoms for generating high-quality faces.','hi',NULL),(1742505141,'What role does the discrete codebook prior play in the CodeFormer method?','The discrete codebook prior in the CodeFormer method reduces the uncertainty of the low-quality to high-quality mapping by casting the restoration task into a finite space of code prediction. The codebook is learned through self-reconstruction of high-quality faces using a vector-quantized autoencoder, which helps to store rich details for face restoration and provides robustness against diverse degradation.','hi',NULL),(1742505142,'What are the benefits of using a Transformer-based network in the CodeFormer method?','The Transformer-based network in the CodeFormer method models the global composition and context of low-quality faces, which helps in accurate code prediction. This global modeling compensates for local information loss in degraded images, enabling the network to recover natural face appearances with high quality and fidelity, even when inputs are severely degraded.','hi',NULL),(1742505143,'How does the Controllable Feature Transformation (CFT) module enhance the adaptability of CodeFormer?','The Controllable Feature Transformation (CFT) module enhances the adaptability of CodeFormer by allowing a flexible trade-off between restoration quality and fidelity. By adjusting an adjustable coefficient, the module controls the information flow from the low-quality encoder to the decoder, enabling the production of high-quality outputs even in cases of heavy degradation by reducing the reliance on degraded input features.','hi',NULL),(1742505144,'What is the main challenge addressed by the proposed CodeFormer method in blind face restoration?','The main challenge addressed by the proposed CodeFormer method is the highly ill-posed problem of blind face restoration, which involves mapping degraded inputs to high-quality outputs and complementing lost high-quality details in the inputs.','hi',NULL),(1742505145,'How does the CodeFormer method utilize a codebook prior to improve face restoration?','The CodeFormer method uses a learned discrete codebook prior in a small proxy space to reduce the uncertainty and ambiguity of restoration mapping by casting blind face restoration as a code prediction task. This approach provides rich visual atoms for generating high-quality faces.','hi',NULL),(1742505146,'What role does the Transformer-based prediction network play in the CodeFormer method?','In the CodeFormer method, the Transformer-based prediction network models the global composition and context of low-quality faces for code prediction. It enables the discovery of natural faces that closely approximate the target faces even when the inputs are severely degraded.','hi',NULL),(1742505147,'What is the purpose of the controllable feature transformation module in the CodeFormer method?','The controllable feature transformation module in the CodeFormer method allows a flexible trade-off between fidelity and quality. It enhances the adaptiveness of the method for different levels of degradation by controlling the information flow from the low-quality encoder to the decoder.','hi',NULL),(1742505148,'How does the CodeFormer method perform compared to state-of-the-art methods in terms of robustness to degradation?','The CodeFormer method outperforms state-of-the-art methods in both quality and fidelity, demonstrating superior robustness to degradation. This is supported by extensive experimental results on synthetic and real-world datasets, verifying the effectiveness of the method.','hi',NULL),(1742505149,'What is the main challenge in blind face restoration that the paper aims to address?','The main challenge in blind face restoration is the highly ill-posed nature of the problem, which involves uncertainty and ambiguity in mapping from low-quality inputs to high-quality outputs, especially when the specific degradation is unknown.','hi',NULL),(1742505150,'How does the proposed CodeFormer model enhance the robustness of face restoration?','CodeFormer enhances robustness by utilizing a learned discrete codebook prior, which reduces the uncertainty of the restoration mapping by casting blind face restoration as a code prediction task. The Transformer-based prediction network models global compositions and context, aiding in recovering natural faces even from severely degraded inputs.','hi',NULL),(1742505151,'What role does the controllable feature transformation module play in the CodeFormer model?','The controllable feature transformation module allows for a flexible trade-off between fidelity and quality in face restoration. It adjusts the information flow from the low-quality encoder to the decoder, which helps in adapting to different levels of input degradation by controlling the balance between detailed high-quality output and maintaining input fidelity.','hi',NULL),(1742505152,'In comparison to existing methods, what advantage does the CodeFormer approach offer?','CodeFormer outperforms existing methods by combining expressive codebook prior with global modeling, leading to superior results in both quality and fidelity. It effectively handles severe degradation by reducing reliance on corrupted input features and eliminating the need for skip connections, which often introduce artifacts.','hi',NULL),(1742505153,'How does the CodeFormer model handle code prediction for face restoration, and what problem does it address?','CodeFormer uses a Transformer-based network to predict code sequences for face restoration. By modeling global interrelations of low-quality faces, it addresses the problem of inaccurate nearest-neighbor matching in codebook lookup due to corrupted textures in degraded inputs, thus providing more reliable and high-quality restoration results.','hi',NULL);
