d. Avoidance of eye contact can imply dishonesty or lack of confidence.\\n\\n3. Facial Expressions: A calm, relaxed expression can portray assurance. Too many exaggerated expressions can make you seem nervous or overly emotional.\\n\\n4. Controlled Gestures: Using your hands and arms to emphasise your points can show passion and excitement about a subject matter. However, overusing or','20250106054752','softskills.pdf',56,'918008142969'),('Soft Skill is a combination of numerous character traits, personal attributes, and other non-technical aspects that influence how well an individual can work or interact with others. Often referred to as people skills or interpersonal skills, here are their usefulness in the professional context and beyond:\\n\\n1. Career Advancement: Soft skills like leadership, teamwork, and strong work ethic can make you stand out from job seekers with comparable hard skills, enhancing your prospects for career advancement.\\n  \\n2. Interpersonal Relationships: Strong interpersonal soft skills such as empathy, patience, and the ability to listen can improve your relationships not only in the office but also in your personal life. \\n  \\n3. Problem Solving: Soft skills such as critical thinking and problem solving help you to deal with challenges','20250106055125','softskills.pdf',56,'918008142969'),('Soft skills, also known as interpersonal or people skills, are personal attributes that determine how you interact with others. These skills are critical for maintaining healthy relationships and managing work effectively. Here are a few soft skills:\\n\\n1. Communication skills: These are fundamental for any interaction. Good communication skills allow individuals to convey information, ideas, or feelings in a clear, respectful, and effective way.\\n\\n2. Teamwork and collaboration: These are essential in any work setting as most tasks are completed in teams or groups. It involves respecting diverse viewpoints, being a team player, and working effectively towards the shared objective.\\n\\n3. Problem-solving: It is about identifying, analyzing, and finding solutions to problems. Good problem-solvers are highly valued in organizations as they help','20250106093916','softskills.pdf',56,'918008142969'),('Response:\\n\\nSure, I can give some insights on the meaning and definition of a communication skill:\\n\\n1. The term \"communication skill\" refers to the ability to understand and convey information effectively and efficiently. \\n\\n2. It not only encompasses verbal and written communication, but also includes non-verbal communication like eye contact, body language, tone of voice, etc.\\n\\n3. Good communication skills involve the ability to listen carefully, clearly articulate one\\\'s ideas or thoughts, present information in an organized manner, and reply or respond constructively.\\n\\n4. For example, a teacher should have effective communication skills to explain complex ideas to students in a way that they can understand. Similarly, in business a manager needs such skills to guide and motivate a team.\\n\\n5.','20250106113232','basicenglish.pdf',60,'918008142969'),('Response:\\n\\nCommunication skills are fundamental for various reasons:\\n\\n1. Personal Development: Effective communication skills help us express our thoughts and feelings effectively, thereby promoting confidence and self-esteem in an individual.\\n\\n2. Career Progression: In a professional setting, excellent communication skills are often valued and recognized, leading to higher career progression opportunities.\\n\\n3. Enhances relationships: In personal or professional life, good communication skills help in building stronger relationships. Knowing when to speak and when to listen can significantly help in resolving conflicts and misunderstandings.\\n\\n4. Problem-Solving: Communication allows people to share their concerns, ideas, and solutions, leading to quicker problem-solving and decision-making actions. \\n\\n5. Teamwork: For effective team collaboration and functioning, communication acts as a glue','20250106113930','basicenglish.pdf',60,'918008142969'),('This document essentially covers a detailed guide about drafting a well-structured, well-formatted, professional report that is also beneficial to the organization and reader. Additionally it outlines tips and elements required for creating a compelling Resume. Here are the key points:\\n\\n1. Quality of a Good Report: The document discusses characteristics of a well-written report, i.e., precision, clarity, relevance, perfect format and how reports add credibility and trust. Clarifies importance of citing accurate and relevant data. It also discusses how it helps in enhancing the writer\'s skills, improves efficiency and helps in decision making process.\\n\\n2. Making a Resume: This document lays bare the purpose of a resume which helps market an individual\'s professionalism, qualifications, skills and relevant experience. It','20250106155903','basicenglish.pdf',60,'919958538194'),('Nouns and pronouns can be used in various places in English sentences. Here are the key areas where you\\\'d typically use nouns and pronouns:\\n\\n1. As Subjects: The noun or pronoun functions as the subject of the sentence. For example, \"Ravi speaks English\" or \"He speaks English\". Here \\\'Ravi\\\' and \\\'He\\\' are the subjects. \\n\\n2. As Objects: The noun or pronoun can act as the object in sentences. For instance, in the sentence \"I love dogs\", \\\'dogs\\\' is the noun which is the object of the sentence. When we replace \\\'dogs\\\' with a pronoun, the sentence becomes \"I love them.\"\\n\\n3. Within Prepositional Phrases: Nouns','20250107084046','basicenglish.pdf',60,'918008142969'),('1. Nouns are names used for identifying people, places, things, or ideas. They are one of the fundamental parts of sentences in English language and grammar.\\n       Example: Peter, Delhi, phone, love, etc. \\n\\n2. Nouns can be broadly categorized into two types - Proper nouns and Common nouns. Proper nouns refer to specific names of people, places or things. For example, Peter, India, Apple Inc. etc. Common nouns are generic names used for a class of people, places or things. For example, man, city, company etc. \\n\\n3. Nouns can be concrete or abstract. Concrete nouns refer to people, places, or things that we can experience through our five senses. For example, dog','20250107084400','basicenglish.pdf',60,'918008142969'),('Verbs are crucial elements of the English language that denote:\\n\\n1. Actions: These are known as action verbs. For example, \"She writes a letter everyday\".\\n\\n2. States of being or existence: These are known as linking or auxiliary verbs. For example, \"She is a doctor\". \\n\\n3. Express conditions or possibilities: These are known as modal verbs. For example, \"We might go to the theatre today\".\\n\\nDifferent types of verbs are used to serve different purposes in a sentence. For example, \"he can swim,\" here \\\'can\\\' is a modal verb expressing the ability to swim.\\n\\nAside from these, there are also verbs that follow certain grammatical rules based on the subject or the idea they are attached to. For example','20250107091537','basicenglish.pdf',60,'918008142969'),('Verbs are one of the most crucial parts of speech in English grammar. They play a significant role in sentences for various reasons such as:\\n\\n1. Expressing Action: Verbs are commonly used to display the actions or activity happening in the sentence. For example, \"Ravi is playing cricket\".\\n2. Indicating State: Verbs can also signify the state or condition of the subject. For example, in the sentence \"Mohan is very kind\", \\\'is\\\' is used as a verb that indicates the state of \\\'Mohan\\\'.\\n3. Showing Occurrence: Some verbs indicate an event or an occurrence. For instance, in the sentence \"The building was destroyed by the earthquake\", \\\'was destroyed\\\' shows an event that had happened','20250107091836','basicenglish.pdf',60,'918008142969'),('Types of body language can be various and cover different aspects such as:\\n\\n1. Posture: This refers to how you stand or sit. A confident person usually portrays an erect and flexible posture, while a person who is not interested or feeling down may slouch or droop their shoulders.\\n\\n2. Head Motion: The movement of your head can say a lot about your interest in the conversation. Nods and shakes can help enhance communication and show that you are engaged.\\n\\n3. Facial Expression: Your face can reveal your feelings in a conversation. For example, if you are angry, fearful, confused, or happy, these emotions will be reflected on your face.\\n\\n4. Eye Contact: Maintaining eye contact while speaking suggests that you are confident and','20250107092157','softskills.pdf',56,'918008142969'),('- Verbs are the action words in a sentence that describe what the subject is doing. They can express a physical action, a mental action, or a state of being. For example, in the sentence \"She runs every morning,\" \\\'runs\\\' is the verb depicting a physical action.\\n- There are three types of verbs; action verbs(e.g., run, eat, write), linking verbs(e.g., is, are, were) which connect the subject of the verb to additional information about the subject and helping verbs (e.g., have, has, had) that help the main verb in a sentence by extending its meaning.\\n- Each verb has five forms: the base form, the -s form, the -ing form, the past','20250107092326','basicenglish.pdf',60,'918008142969'),('Verbs are essential elements of the English language that express:\\n \\n- Actions: For example, \"She runs every morning\", \"He is reading a book\".\\n \\n- States or conditions: For example, \"I am happy\" or \"They are in the park\".\\n \\n- Occurrences: For example, \"A party is taking place at Jessica\\\'s house\" or \"An accident happened on my way to work.\"\\n\\nPrimary or main verbs have significant meaning on their own, whereas auxiliary verbs, also known as helping verbs, support the main verb to denote actions or states. For example, in the sentence \"He is running\", \"running\" is the main verb and \"is\" is the auxiliary verb.\\n\\nVerbs also signify the tense (past','20250107092755','basicenglish.pdf',60,'918008142969'),('Verbs are an essential part of the English language. They can be categorized as:\\n\\n1. Main Verbs or Action Verbs: These verbs express specific actions. For example, \'run\', \'play\', \'eat\', etc.\\n   \\n2. Auxiliary Verbs or Helping Verbs: These verbs are used with the main verb to help complete the sentence or indicate a certain time frame. They include \'is\', \'am\', \'was\', \'were\', \'be\', \'have\', \'do\', etc.\\n   \\n3. Modal Verbs or Modal Auxiliary Verbs: These verbs express necessity, likelihood, ability, and permission. They include \'can\', \'could\', \'may\', \'might\', \'shall\', \'should\', \'will\',','20250107092914','basicenglish.pdf',60,'918008142969'),('1. The document focuses on how to write impactful Curriculum Vitae and Resumes, and can be used by candidates or employees pursuing job opportunities in India.\\n2. It emphasizes the use of simple fonts, accurate information, correct grammar and punctuation, and the necessity of highlighting achievements rather than subjective accounts.\\n3. The document distinguishes between a Curriculum Vitae and a Resume, the former offering a more comprehensive summary of one\'s educational background and work experience, while the latter is a succinct summation of relevant qualifications and skills.\\n4. It highlights the value of testimonials, and the importance of including credible references who can vouch for the competency of the candidate.\\n5. The document also provides a list of self-assessed questions for readers to gauge their','20250107200002','softskills.pdf',56,'918420925890'),('1. This document provides a guide for creating effective resumes and CVs. It details the dos and don\'ts of resume writing, stressing on importance of factual, complete, and objective information. \\n\\n2. It suggests avoiding fancy fonts, but encourages the use of capital letters or underlines for headings. \\n\\n3. The document insists on proper grammar, spelling, vocabulary, and punctuation, and also emphasizes the importance of actual achievements and skills over subjective accounts. \\n\\n4. It also provides key terms like \'Curriculum Vitae\', \'Resume\', \'Testimonial\', and \'references/referees\', outlining their meanings and relevance in the job application process.\\n\\n5. The document also consists of self-assessment questions and further reading recommendations for deeper understanding','20250107200240','softskills.pdf',56,'918420925890'),('1. The document provides essential guidelines on crafting a Curriculum Vitae (CV) or Resume. It includes:\\n   - Keeping your CV factual, complete, objective, and error-free.\\n   - Reflecting your skills or achievements without any subjective accounts.\\n   - Ensuring the accuracy of your personal details like address, phone number, and date.\\n   - Paying attention to grammar, vocabulary, and punctuation. \\n   - Including references who can give positive feedback about you. \\n\\n2. A CV or a Resume is essentially a summary of an individual\'s work experience, educational background, and other qualifications. A testimonial can reinforce your skills and experience, making you an attractive candidate to potential employers. \\n\\n3. The document also suggests writing a cover','20250107200521','softskills.pdf',56,'918420925890'),('This is a detailed document providing a comprehensive guide for individuals who are looking to create an effective resume or CV. Here are some points highlighted in the document:\\n\\n1. It emphasizes the importance of using simple and legible font in resume/CV. Avoid using fancy fonts, italics or all capital letters. Make sure each section is clearly identifiable with appropriate headings.\\n\\n2. The document provides guidance on how to compile a factual, objective, and complete resume/CV. This includes ensuring correct personal details like address, contact numbers, and date.\\n\\n3. The document stresses that your CV should reflect your skills, achievements and experience instead of subjective narratives.\\n\\n4. It talks about the importance of testimonials and references in a CV, stating that these are great','20250107203216','softskills.pdf',56,'918420925890'),('To apply for an MSME loan in India, follow these steps:\\n\\n1. Go to the official website for the lender. In this case, visit Equitas Bank’s MSME loan page at https://www.equitasbank.com/business-banking/finance-your-business/working-capital/loan-finance-msme-loan/\\n\\n2. Look for the \"Apply Now\" button and click on it to start the application process. \\n\\n3. Complete the application form. This typically involves providing information about the business, the amount you want to borrow, and how you plan to use the funds. \\n\\n4. Be sure to attach all necessary documents as mentioned in the checklist provided. Documentation usually includes financial statements, tax returns, and legal documents about your business. \\n\\n5. Submit your application for review. Equitas Bank promises to notify applicants of their decision within specified timelines based on the credit limit applied.\\n\\n6. If your loan is approved, you would need to pay a processing fee, which could be up to 2% of the loan amount, and a non-refundable proposal login fee of Rs. 5000/-.\\n\\nPlease note that the lender will also evaluate the creditworthiness of the business and its owners, so it’s important to maintain a good credit history. \\n\\nIs there anything else I can assist you with? You can ask me about other loan types or the specifics of the MSME loan terms and conditions.','20250109120918','msmeloans.pdf',65,'919830619658'),('Setting up a jewellery shop in Pune or any city requires careful planning and execution. Here are some steps that you can follow:\\n\\n1. *Market Research:* The first step is to conduct a thorough market research to understand the jewellery preferences in Pune. This includes understanding the major competitor\'s product range, pricing, and promotional strategies.\\n\\n2. *Location Selection:* Choose a location that is easily accessible and is frequented by your target customers. Prime areas such as Laxmi Road, Pimpri, and Koregaon Park have a good footfall for jewellery shoppers.\\n\\n3. *Licenses and Registration:* Ensure you have all the required licenses and compliance regulations met, including GST registration and registration from the Bureau of Indian Standards (BIS).\\n\\n4. *Store Frontage:* Make sure that your store frontage is appealing and eye-catching. Use illuminated signage and showcase your key jewellery pieces at the front window.\\n\\n5. *Offer a Unique Selling Proposition (USP):* The market is crowded, so aim to offer something uniquely attractive to your potential customers. This could be in terms of bespoke designs, competitive pricing, or exceptional customer service.\\n\\n6. *Advertise:* Consider investing in advertisements and promotions to generate visibility and pull in customers. Localized digital marketing can be especially effective.\\n\\n7. *Training Staff:* Train your staff to be knowledgeable and courteous to provide excellent customer experience.\\n\\n8. *Build a Website:* Establish an online presence with a professional website showcasing your product range. Provide an option for online consultation and purchase to cater to the growing trend of digital shopping.\\n\\nUnfortunately, I don\'t have the specifics on the licences and the regulations in Pune right now. You can reach out to me on [website](https://www.yogyabano.com/contact-us) where I can provide you tailor-made responses to your specific queries. \\n\\nWould you like to know more about how to manage the operations of your jewellery shop in Pune or any other jewellery related queries?','20250109121331','jewelleryretail.pdf',65,'919830619658'),('A loan is:\\n\\n1. A sum of money that is borrowed from a financial institution like a bank, credit union or online lender which you are obliged to pay back with interest over a set timeframe. \\n2. The main types of loans are personal loans, home loans, student loans, auto loans, and small business loans.\\n3. Each type of loan may have a different purpose, for example, a home loan is for buying a house, a student loan is for covering educational expenses, and an auto loan is for buying a vehicle.\\n4. Loans usually require the borrower to make fixed monthly payments including the principal amount and interest until the loan is entirely repaid.\\n5. For instance, MSME loans provided by Equitas in India offer specially tailored financial solutions for micro, small and medium-sized businesses which can be used for a variety of purposes such as capital requirements, plant, machinery, equipment purchase etc.\\n6. Loans are usually provided based on the borrower\'s creditworthiness, which is assessed on the basis of the borrower\'s credit history, income level, and other factors.\\n\\nI hope this gives you a basic understanding of what a loan is. If you have more questions, feel free to ask – I\'m here to help.','20250109122242','msmeloans.pdf',65,'919830619658'),('MSME stands for Micro, Small and Medium Enterprises. In the Indian context, the enterprises are classified on the basis of investment made in plant and machinery if they are operating in the manufacturing sector and on the basis of investment made in equipment for enterprises engaged in providing or rendering of services. \\n\\nHere are some key insights about MSMEs:\\n\\n1. The MSME sector contributes significantly to India\'s economy, driving innovation, employment, and socio-economic growth. \\n\\n2. Enterprises are classified into Micro, Small, and Medium enterprises based on their investment in plant and machinery (for manufacturing units) or equipment (for service providers).\\n\\n3. Micro Enterprises are those where investment does not exceed Rs. 1 crore and turnover is less than Rs. 5 crores. \\n\\n4. Small Enterprises are those where investment ranges between Rs. 1 crore and Rs. 10 crores, and turnover is between Rs. 5 crores and Rs. 50 crores.\\n\\n5. Medium Enterprises are those where the investment is between Rs. 10 crores to Rs. 50 crores and turnover ranges from Rs. 50 crores to Rs. 250 crores.\\n\\n6. MSME Loans are offered to these enterprises to aid in their smooth functioning and growth. The loans can be used for a variety of purposes such as upgrading infrastructure, scaling operations, inventory management etc.\\n\\n7. Equitas Bank in India, for example, offers MSME loans with specially tailored financial solutions, catering to the “Missing Middle” segment in India\'s economic growth.\\n\\nRemember, the main objective of the MSME Loan is to facilitate the growth of the enterprise by providing them with necessary financial aid. If you have any more questions or require clarification about MSMEs or MSME loans, please feel free to ask. You may also want to know about the application process and terms for MSME loans, can I assist you with that?','20250109123410','msmeloans.pdf',65,'919830619658'),('Sales can be described as follows: \\n\\n1. Sales is the process of selling goods or services to customers. This activity is carried out by salespeople who engage in various strategies to encourage prospective customers to purchase their product or service. \\n\\n2. In a wider context, it is not just about exchanging products or services for money but it also involves building strong relationships with customers. Good salespeople are experts at understanding customer needs and presenting their product or service as the solution. \\n\\n3. Sales also involves understanding and managing the sales process which includes steps like prospecting, initiating contact, identifying and understanding needs, presenting solutions, handling objections, closing the sale and follow-up service.\\n\\n4. A commonly recognized advantage of a sales career is its lucrative financial rewards, as it is often performance-based. The more you sell, the more you earn. \\n\\n5. Sales jobs often require traveling and taking on considerable responsibility. Salespeople may also need to be open to relocation, depending on the nature of the work. \\n\\n6. Another aspect of sales is the need for continuous learning and adaptation. As consumer behaviors change, so does the art of selling. Salespeople must keep abreast of new sales techniques and changes in their industry to remain competitive. \\n\\nWould you like to know about the qualities required to succeed in sales or the various challenges faced in a sales role? Please feel free to ask.','20250110121855','sales.pdf',67,'919830619658'),('Here is the step-by-step guide to learning the best practices in sustainable construction techniques:\\n\\n1. Rigorous Course Study: The foremost step is enrolling yourself in a credible course on sustainable construction techniques. A good such example is our Construction & Real Estate course.\\n\\n2. Hands-on Experience: Practical implementation of learned concepts is necessary. Assess if options for interships or on-site training are available with your course.\\n\\n3. Participate in Assessments: Take full advantage of assessments provided in the course. This will help in identifying the areas of improvement.\\n\\n4. Keep Revisiting Lessons: Revisit the lessons periodically to refresh your knowledge and stay updated with new additions, if any.\\n\\n5. Seeking Feedback: Seek regular feedback from mentors or experienced professionals in the field. Feedback can help to clarify doubts and correct mistakes.\\n\\n6. Engage in Discussion: Engage yourself in discussions about sustainable practices and regulations in construction. Forums and networking sites can be helpful for this.\\n\\n7. Updated with Industry: The construction industry is continually evolving in terms of sustainable practices. Keeping up to speed with industry trends can have a significant impact on your understanding and application of best practices.\\n\\nFeel free to ask further questions about any of the points above. Do you need clarification on any specific areas of sustainable construction practices?\\n','20250113131340','constructiontechniques.pdf',69,'917327025607'),('The tools to learn Sustainable Construction Techniques vary and significantly depend on the specific area of focus. However, here are a few tools often used in the industry:\\n\\n1. **Green Building Software:** Tools like Sefaira, GBS Pro, or Concept Parametric Design Tool can guide you in designing and implementing sustainable construction projects.\\n   \\n2. **Design Software:** The likes of CAD (Computer-Aided Design), Revit and BIM (Building Information Modelling) software helps in designing energy-efficient buildings.\\n   \\n3. **Life-Cycle Assessment Tools:** Tools such as Athena Impact Estimator for Buildings, LCA Calculator, or GaBi are needed for assessing the environmental impact of a building from its inception to its demolition.\\n   \\n4. **Energy Analysis Tools:** The likes of HAP (Hourly Analysis Program), Energy Plus, Matchup are frequently used for conducting sophisticated building energy analysis.\\n   \\n5. **Project Management Software:** Software like Procore or Aconex helps in managing sustainable construction projects by providing features for document management, budgeting, and scheduling.\\n\\n6. **Books and Online Resources:** There is an abundance of books and online resources that provide in-depth knowledge about the principles of sustainable construction and various practices and technologies employed around the world.\\n\\n7. **Workshops and Seminars:** Ongoing learning from offline or online workshops and seminars can bolster one\'s understanding of sustainable construction techniques.\\n\\nRemember, successful sustainable construction is not just about using the right tool, but understanding and employing the principles behind the project. So, focus on reinforcing your principles and your proficiency in these tools will follow. \\n\\nFeel free to ask if you have further questions or need clarification on any of these tools.','20250113131444','constructiontechniques.pdf',69,'917327025607'),('The digital health tools referred to in the course are:\\n\\n1. Telemedicine: Enables doctors to consult with patients online over video chats, reducing the need for physical consultations.\\n\\n2. Electronic Health Records: Facilitates proper storage and easy access of patient medical information for better treatment and care.\\n\\n3. Patient Monitoring Systems: Employs digital tools to oversee patient\'s health data in real-time, either within hospitals or remotely. This allows healthcare professionals to keep a close eye on the patient\'s health and take immediate action whenever necessary. \\n\\n4. Digital Therapeutics: Engage patients in their healthcare journey via evidence-based therapeutic interventions driven by high-quality software programs to prevent, manage, or treat a broad spectrum of behavioral, mental, and physical diseases. \\n\\n5. Health Information Exchange (HIE): Offers a secure method for sharing healthcare information electronically amongst providers, enabling them to have more informed conversations, thus improving patient care. \\n\\nAgain, these are general examples and the specific tools may vary depending on the healthcare environment and patient needs. \\n\\nI hope this information was helpful! If you have any other questions about digital health or any other topics, feel free to ask.','20250114040002','digitalhealth.pdf',70,'917327025607'),('Welding is a fabrication process that involves joining materials, typically metals or thermoplastics, by causing coalescence. Here are further details:\\n\\n- Welding uses high heat to melt the parts together and allow them to cool, resulting in fusion. Welding is distinct from lower temperature metal-joining techniques such as brazing and soldering, which do not melt the base metal.\\n\\n- It is classified into two groups: fusion welding, which uses heat alone or pressure welding, which uses heat and pressure.\\n\\n- There are several types of fusion welding including electric arc, gas, and thermit. Electric arc welding is the most commonly used type and it uses an electric arc to melt the base and filler metals.\\n\\n- Other common methods are Gas or oxy-fuel welding which uses a flame to melt metal and Oxy-fuel and plasma cutting which involve the melting of metal and the generation of airborne metal fume. \\n\\n- During welding, precautions should be taken to avoid health hazards like electric shock, fire, explosion and exposure to toxic fumes.\\n\\n- Welding requires skills and proper training as it is commonly used to fabricate or repair parts in various industries like automotive, construction and manufacturing.\\n\\nI hope this information was helpful. Do you have any more questions about welding or other career paths in manufacturing, construction or engineering that you would like to ask?','20250120122550','weldernew.pdf',72,'9876543210_4'),('Due to the nature of the request, I can\'t provide a specific response to a text file or document. However, I can assist you with some generalized coaching advice related to strong wood connection procedures:\\n\\n1. Always ensure safety: Whether you are using nails or glue, ensuring safety by clamping and securing the wood pieces is essential. Use the right tools for clamping and wear personal protective equipment, such as safety glasses and gloves.\\n\\n2. Selection of nails: Make sure the size and type of the nails are appropriate. If unsure, seek advice or refer to the manual/guide provided. Always pre-drill holes if the nails are too large to avoid damaging the wood.\\n\\n3. Using wood glue: Preparation is key. The surfaces to be glued must be clean, dry, and smooth for an effective bond. Apply an even layer of the adhesive and avoid using excess glue as it can weaken the bond.\\n\\n4. Drying and Curing: After applying the glue or inserting the nails, let them dry or cure as per the recommended time. Rushing this process can result in a weakened connection.\\n\\n5. Learning Resources: Use the provided resources like http://www.eﬁ-costarica.com/antique-furniture-joints.html, http://woodworking.about.com/od/joinery/tp/JoineryHub.htm, and http://www.technologystudent.com/joints/joindex.htm to learn about the different types of woods, tools, and joints.\\n\\nIf you have a more specific question or need guidance on a particular aspect of woodworking, I would encourage you to reach out at https://www.yogyabano.com/contact-us. I\'m here to guide you with all your career-related queries.\\n\\nDo you have more questions regarding woodworking techniques or any career-related query? I\'d be happy to help!','20250129055551','woodjoints.pdf',52,'918008142969'),('Based on the fact that I can\\\'t access or analyze the content of the link you provided, here are some general tips for making\"strong wood connection\" using nails and wood glue :\\n\\nUsing nails -\\n1. Mark and align both pieces accurately before starting.\\n2. Always pre-clamp and secure your wood pieces for better alignment and stability.\\n3. For large nails, pre-drill a hole to guide your nail; it will decrease the chances of splits or cracks.\\n4. Sink your nail head a bit under the surface to provide a neat finish and better adherence.\\n5. Never force a nail into your wood, it can cause damage or weaken the connected spot.\\n\\nUsing wood glue - \\n1. Prepare the wood surface by sanding it and cleaning the dust off before applying glue for better adherence.\\n2. Apply an even, thin layer of glue on both surfaces to be connected. More glue doesn\\\'t necessarily mean a stronger bond.\\n3. Secure and clamp your pieces together until the glue dries completely. Each glue has its own drying time, refer to its guide.\\n\\nI hope these tips help you. If you have any more specific questions, feel free to ask!\\n\\nFor further resources, you might like to explore these articles:\\n\\n- [Furniture Joints](http://www.efi-costarica.com/antique-furniture-joints.html)\\n- [Overview of woodworking joints](http://www.technologystudent.com/joints/joindex.htm)\\n- [Common woodworking joints](http://www.raygirling.com/wwjoints.htm)\\n- [Exotic wood](http://www.macbeath.com)\\n- [Overview of woodworking tools](http://www.technologystudent.com/equip1/equipex1.htm)\\n\\nAs a career coach, I\\\'m here to help you overcome any challenges you may face in your career. If unsure or need more guidance, kindly contact me on [https://www.yogyabano.com/contact-us](https://www.yogyabano.com/contact-us) and I would be glad to assist!\\n\\nIn case my general advice doesn\\\'t fit your specific query, could you please rephrase or elaborate on it?','20250129055746','woodjoints.pdf',52,'918008142969'),('Response:\\n\\n1. You are advised to dress professionally for work. Steer clear of casual wear like jeans, capris shorts, and sleeveless shirts, and instead opt for formal clothes in neutral hues that fit comfortably and are clean and ironed.\\n\\n2. Be mindful of how you express yourself at work. Refrain from negative behaviour such as blaming others, getting involved in workplace politics, or criticising your colleagues. Practice communication that is respectful and solution-oriented.\\n\\n3. Maintain a tidy workspace. Dispose of unnecessary stationery and keep your files organized for easier access. Additionally, ensure that your work station is switched off before wrapping up for the day.\\n\\n4. Avoid personal indulgences like eating food noisily or dressing too extravagantly at work. Females are advised to stick to minimal makeup, and all should avoid strong perfumes, and inappropriate or overly casual attire.\\n\\n5. Workplace communication etiquette is crucial. Always attend meetings with note-taking materials, keep your supervisors informed through emails, and respect communication boundaries established by the organization.\\n\\n6. Consider proper time management a priority, whether it\'s arriving at the office on time or ensuring you\'re prepared for meetings. \\n\\n7. Lastly, respect the property of the organization. Do not bring home any office stationery as it is equivalent to stealing. \\n\\nTo learn more on this or any other career-related aspect, feel free to ask any other questions. I am here to help!','20250129101732','softskills.pdf',56,'918008142969'),('This \"course\" is not necessarily a formal course but rather a comprehensive guide for individuals with strong backgrounds in coaching and career counselling, particularly those who have substantial experience in mentoring young professionals and aspiring individuals in India. The emphasis of the guide is on:\n\n1. Outlining tailored products and services: The guide provides information on how banks can create awareness about their varied offerings tailored to different customer segments. This could include organising workshops, seminars, etc., to engage with potential customers.\n\n2. Suggesting training programs focusing on vital business areas: Training programs in areas like HR, financial management, business management, and marketing are discussed in this guide, particularly how these can enhance the skills of women entrepreneurs.\n\n3. Explaining MSME toolkit: It provides an understanding of how an MSME toolkit can aid businesses at different stages - inception, startup, and growth. It highlights how less privileged women-owned businesses can benefit from these readily and freely available resources.\n\n4. Fostering an enabling environment: The guide focuses on how creating a welcoming business environment can accelerate the growth of women-led businesses. It discusses aspects like risk capital fund, equal rights to property, simplifying collateral requirements, and formulating women-focused policies.\n\n5. Incorporating the role of DFIs (Development Finance Institutions): It emphasizes how DFIs can offer credit lines and equity schemes to commercial banks to meet the needs of women entrepreneurs whilst also mitigating risks associated with lending to this segment.\n\n6. Promoting online customer support: The importance and relevance of an online customer support ecosystem, such as call centres for women entrepreneurs, is also stressed upon.\n\n7. Offering a roadmap: Lastly, the guide encapsulates ways to calculate the financing gap for women-owned MSMEs based on comprehensive assessments of the financing needs.\n\nWould you like more details about any of the areas that were discussed, or do you have any other questions related to the guide? I\'m here to help!','20250304110703','improvingwomen.pdf',75,'918008142969'),('This course is designed to provide guidance and tools for people with strong coaching and career counseling credentials, with a primary focus on understanding the challenges and opportunities women entrepreneurs face in India.  \n\n- The course details the importance of awareness about tailored products and services available for women entrepreneurs and how to access them. \n- It involves training sessions on human resources, financial management, business management, marketing, and venture financing to support women entrepreneurs in sustaining and growing their enterprises. \n- It offers a toolkit to guide women-owned businesses at different stages of growth, from inception to maturation, in business planning, financial projections, input management, marketing, market linkages, and branding. \n- The course discusses the role of government and multilateral agencies in providing risk capital funds and other financial facilities to encourage women entrepreneurship.\n- The content emphasises on easing collateral requirements,