nteractions for mutual learning and networking opportunities.\n\n6. Practical Exposure: Gain on-ground exposure to real situations and challenges faced by young employees and candidates in India, and the most effective ways of guiding them. \n\nI would be happy to provide more specific details based on your interests. Do you have any other questions or aspects you would like to discuss further?','20250304111400','improvingwomen.pdf',75,'918008142969'),('In response to your query, it seems there is some missing information about the specific object or context for which the dimensions are being asked. Here are some general dimensions associated with the topic of fire safety training:\n\n1. Knowledge Dimension: This relates to the key fire safety concepts, basic principles of fire containment, and understanding various fire categories like Class A, B, C, D fires etc.\n\n2. Skill Dimension: This refers to practical fire safety skills such as the use of fire extinguishers, following the P.A.S.S method (Pull, Aim, Squeeze, Sweep), and managing fire evacuation procedures.\n\n3. Understanding Dimension: These are the insights about common fire hazards, potential ignition sources, and the importance of regular maintenance of safety equipment.\n\n4. Compliance Dimension: This refers to the official standards and regulations like OSHA Fire Prevention Rule 1910.38(a) that companies must adhere to for ensuring fire safety at the workplace.\n\n5. Awareness Dimension: This involves promoting employee awareness related to fire safety protocols, emergency evacuation plans, and fire hazard prevention strategies.\n\nHowever, I\'m unable to provide specific dimensions as your query is a bit vague. Could you please provide more details? You can get a specific response for your query by reaching me at https://www.yogyabano.com/contact-us. \n\nFeel free to ask more questions to enhance your understanding of fire safety norms and their implementation.','20250321093943','weldernew.pdf',76,'9876543210_4'),('This lesson provides valuable information on a variety of topics, including:\n\n1. Electrical Safety: The lesson outlines the effects of current flow, potential hazards like arc flash and arc blast, as well as measures to ensure safety such as the use of personal protective equipment (PPE) and appropriate earthing systems. \n\n2. Safe Distribution Systems: It covers information on the safe distribution of electricity, including the setup and maintenance of distribution boards and circuit separation.\n\n3. Legal Requirements: The lesson touches upon several legal requirements for maintaining electrical safety. For instance, the installation of appropriate circuit breakers and the use of ISI standard wires for internal house wiring.\n\n4. Tools and Testing Equipment: It provides an overview of the appropriate tools and testing equipment for electrical work.\n\n5. Current Leakage: Some insights are also provided on how to prevent and detect current leakage in electrical systems.\n\nIf you would like to learn more about a particular topic, please feel free to ask!','20250508130752','housewiring.pdf',78,'918008142969'),('This lesson is primarily about:\n1. The importance of understanding electrical safety and precautions when dealing with electricity and electrical appliances.\n2. The different factors affecting electric current flow and its effects on the human body.\n3. Different types of electrical shocks and dangers including arc flash and arc blast.\n4. The concept of earthing and its importance along with safe distribution systems.\n5. Discussions on the necessary legal requirements concerning electrical safety.\n6. Importance of using Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) when dealing with electricity.\n7. The rules laid down by the Central Electricity Authority (CEA) regarding precautionary measures before a connection is established.\n\nThis a comprehensive lesson aiming to equip you with the knowledge required to deal with electricity safely. If you have any other questions or need further clarification on any topics, feel free to ask.','20250512054246','housewiring.pdf',78,'918008142969'),('Installing solar PV on a rooftop is a technical process, but here\'s a simplified step-by-step guide:\n\n1. **Site Evaluation**: The first step involves assessing the suitability of the site where the solar PV system is to be installed. This involves considering factors such as sunlight exposure, roof condition, and space availability.\n\n2. **System Design:** Based on the site evaluation, a solar PV system must be designed to appropriately capture and convert sunlight into electricity.\n\n3. **Municipal Approval:** In most areas, the local governing body would need to approve of the installation. You\'d need to abide by specific construction codes.\n\n4. **Installation of Mounts:** Mounts are then installed to secure the solar panels to the roof. They need to be installed correctly aligning with the south for the maximum sunlight capture.\n\n5. **Installation of Solar Panels:** Solar panels, connected by a series of wires, are then installed on these mounts.\n  \n6. **System wiring and Inverter installion:** The solar panels are then wired together and connected to an inverter. This inverter converts DC power produced by the solar panels into AC electricity that your home can use.\n\n7. **System Testing:** Finally, test your system to ensure everything is correctly installed and working.\n\nRemember, the entire solar PV installation process requires technical expertise and should only be handled by trained professionals for safety and efficiency.\n\nI hope this information is helpful. If you have any further questions on solar PV installation, please feel free to ask.\n\nIs there something else you would like to know about solar energy or installation details? You can always refer to our website https://www.yogyabano.com/contact-us for more details and specific responses to your queries.','20250513103816','solarinstallation.pdf',77,'918008142969'),('The Basic Welding Technical Learning College course is structured as follows:\n\n1. Flexible Schedule: The program is designed with a flexible scheduling system, where individuals can study at their own pace and pick what time works best for them.\n\n2. Course Design: The courses are delivered online in combination with traditional textbooks. The syllabus, course content, assignments, and post-examinations are all available online.\n\n3. Personalized Guidance: Once enrolled, a Personal Student Service Representative will guide each student on an individual basis throughout the course. Subject Matter Experts are also assigned for each course to ensure academic support.\n\n4. CEU Course: This continuing education course provides comprehensive training in basic electric, gas welding, cutting safety principles, fire prevention, and understanding Right-to-Know and OSHA fire regulations.\n\n5. Course Completion: Upon completion of the course, students will receive a certificate of completion via mail. There is rush option available for an additional fee.\n\nWould you like to know anything more about the course duration, enrollment process, prerequisites, or course fee?','20250619163920','weldernew.pdf',76,'918420925890');
